<item>
            <title>[LU-2353] Tests mount servers as ldiskfs</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-2353</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Several tests attempt to mount the server filesystems as ldiskfs to check that certain files exist.  This can still be done with zfs servers but they should be mounted with &apos;zfs mount&apos; after clearing the canmount property.  This work also depends on sorting out the remaining ZPL compatibility issues so all the server objects will appear in the ZPL namespace.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
